{
  "texts": [
    "The use of hybrid models in natural language understanding and generation has been investigated, with the aim of creating systems that can understand and generate human-like text while adhering to logical constraints [53], [54].",
    "Efforts have been made to develop hybrid models for decision-making tasks in uncertain environments, leveraging the strengths of both approaches to handle ambiguity and incomplete information [55], [56], [57].",
    "The application of hybrid models in robotics has been another area of focus, particularly in tasks that require both sensory data processing and logical decisionmaking [56], [58], [59].",
    "Research has also explored the use of hybrid models in predictive analytics, aiming to create systems that can make accurate predictions based on complex datasets while incorporating domain-specific rules and knowledge [60], [61], [62].",
    "The potential of hybrid models in enhancing the interpretability and trustworthiness of AI systems has been a key consideration, with studies aiming to create models that are not only effective but also transparent and explainable [63], [64]."
  ]
}